So many people asked me apurva why u wearing slippers so I had fallen from first floor by stairs in a designers showroom just before 3 days traveling for iifa to @visitabudhabi and I had to do the #greencarpet walk. I was advised to take rest. So had gone to the airport in a wheelchair but during 3 days I was running working in the pain. My focus was and is clear. Luckily bumped into @beingsalmankhan sir at Mumbai Airport departure for @etihad my flight outside lounge and he was so motivating that when he saw my betadine on my knees. He said u will do it  then met #salmankhan sir Backstage and believe me he was just motivating nothing else. Even though had bumped into him in many parties before but in actuality saw the goodness in him by interacting with him though very little but it was beautiful. Manifesting to share screen space with him soon #inshallah universe listening 🎶 ✨️ ❤️ ♥️ 💕 💖

Well previously when I was a child and have grown up in such a family wherein I had gotten everything whatever I wanted materialistic expensive Toys one of d best schools dresses footwear everything so for me Money was very secondary as I didn't knw d importance and then I was too naive. As u knw how marwadi over sanskari mom keeps u and makes sure u think u r too destitute a person lol irrespective of having everything to make u grounded.. even after everything a very overly middle class values for which I couldn't thank them enough. Agreed!
But then while growing up in different cities of India be it anywhere and infact different countries and when I started working on my own for my self ego and confidence I had realized how imp money is and in the robot rather rat race and quandary dilemma had quenched for more and more fame and self earned money. But then something happened so rude to me. Had cried a lot a lot a lot.. had taken a lot of emotions out. Cathartic. Understood how world is. Understood why ma pa had kept Me in a shell. Was no 1 in studies in college a1 grades in @newyorkfilmacademy too had best A1+++ grades as I always wanted to be no 1 that's all in whatever I do. Without even an #ayahuasca I felt like everything is tossing around may be cos I was too much in something but believe me coming out of it feels so so #liberating better than anything anyone. I gave my 100% in whatever m wanting to be and finally a big news out soon. #inshallah

Well what more to pen!! Huh!! :):)

Last but not d least finally understood after these waves that nothing is important than love peace of mind ✨️👌🏻 ❤️ 
I love #maalakshmi and definitely want to prosper and rise high but never at the cost of anything. Def wants #Lakshmi always but read between d lines. Never did do or will do anything to gain fame and money and I take unabashedly pride in it. Proud kabhi hua nahi pride hamesha :):)
